notesStmt.note: Folios damaged at the beginning and at the end.
Folio 34r: a partly illegible contract of purchase.
Yehudah ben Mosheh ben Se῾adyah ben Avraham ha-Leṿi of San῾a: inscribed, folio 34r and in the colophon, folio 138v.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A service book, according to the Yemenite rite, with the books of Psalms and Proverbs prefixed.

supportDesc.foliation: Folios 1-33 have a separate Hebrew foliation (from 63 onwards, folios 34-95 being numbered 1-62).

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 31; written lines: 31; Uniform layout. Visible mastara ruling. Initial words written in larger characters. Leaf catchwords on every verso. Numerous marginal notes and additions.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 17th century, puctuated. Shalom ben Daṿid ben Yitsḥaḳ ben Shelomoh ben Ya῾aḳov Al-Ḥag᾿ani: inscribed, folio 138v.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Prayer Book. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2417.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: N. Mavrocordato: purchased by the British Museum from him on 08 October 1881: inscribed, folio [157v].
